ELISA Function

ELISAmodelfit <- function(OD) {
## ELISA model fit
#Fit a 4-parameter model from the standard curve in order to identify the correct paramaters of a formula to convert fluorescence to aldosterone concentrations.
# Subtract background signal (measured at 540nm) from target signal (measured at 450nm)
OD$corrected <- OD$OD_450 - OD$OD_540

standards <- OD %>% filter(grepl("std", Sample)) # one way of creating a new tibble that only contains your standards

nsb <- OD %>% filter(grepl("nsb", Sample)) # one way of creating a new tibble that only contains your NSBs

# create a tibble for the actual concentrations by std name -> this has conc for aldosterone kit.
stdcrvdata <- data.frame(
  Sample=paste0("std",rep(seq(1,7,1),each=2)),
  known=rep(c(4000,1000,250,62.25,15.625,3.906,0),each=2)
  )

# sort standards by name to match the order of 'stdcrvdata' data.
standards <- standards %>% arrange(Sample) %>% dplyr::select(c(Sample,corrected))

# sort stdcrvdata by name to match the order of 'standards' data.
stdcrvdata <- stdcrvdata %>% arrange(Sample)

# combine them together
stdcrvdata <- data.frame(standards,expected=stdcrvdata$known)
colnames(stdcrvdata)[2] <- "measured"

# take out zeros
stdcrvdata <- stdcrvdata %>% filter(expected > 0)
stdcrvdata$logconc <-log10(stdcrvdata$expected)# log10 from conc

# plot(stdcrvdata$logconc, stdcrvdata$measured)
# model the standard curve using generated points.  plot those points in red.
fit <- drm(formula =   measured ~ logconc , data = stdcrvdata, fct = LL.4())
summary(fit)

# This is a description of the variables and terms defined in the 'fit' model.
# x = the independent variable (Absorbance) (Concentration, estimated from the Absorbance)
# y = the dependent variable 
# The 4 estimated parameters consist of the following:

# the minimum value that can be obtained. (this is the ABS at conc. 0)
# a = fit$coefficients[2] 
# d = the maximum value that can be obtained (i.e. what happens at infinite dose)
# c = the point of inflection (i.e. the point on the S shaped curve halfway between a and d)
# b = Hill’s slope of the curve (i.e. this is related to the steepness of the curve at point c).

# Generate points from  model. Pick range from logconc
x <- seq(from = 0, to = 4, length=100)

# from OD ~ d + (a - d)/(1 + (logconc/cc)^b)
y <- (fit$coefficients[2]+ (fit$coefficients[3]- fit$coefficients[2])/(1+(x/fit$coefficients[4])^ fit$coefficients[1])) 
# remove standards and NSB wells leaving only experimental measurements
OD <- OD %>% filter(!grepl("std|nsb", Sample))

# here we are applying the equation described in ELISAmodelfit function to...
OD$loganswer<- fit$coefficients[4]*(
  (
    (-1* fit$coefficients[3]+ OD$corrected)/
      (fit$coefficients[2]-OD$corrected))^(1/ fit$coefficients[1])
  )

OD$conc <- 10^OD$loganswer

OD$below <- OD$conc < min(stdcrvdata$expected)
OD$above <- OD$conc > max(stdcrvdata$expected)

plot(x = stdcrvdata$logconc, y = stdcrvdata$measured, main="log standard curve",
  xlim = c(min(x),max(x)),
  ylim = c(min(y),max(y))
     )
lines(x,y, lty="dotted", col="red")
lines(OD$loganswer, OD$corrected, type="points", col="blue")

OD$Sample <- gsub(pattern = "mediaOnly", replacement = "media_NA", x = OD$Sample)

OD <- separate(data = OD, col = Sample, into = c("tx","Dox"), sep = "_")

OD$Dox <- relevel(factor(OD$Dox), ref = "ND")
OD$tx <- relevel(factor(OD$tx), ref = "DMSO")

bg <- OD %>% filter(tx=="media") %>% summarise(mean(na.omit(conc))) %>% pull()
OD$conc <- OD$conc - bg

OD <- OD %>% filter(tx!="media")
OD$tx <- gsub(x = OD$tx, pattern = "uM", replacement = "")
levels(factor(OD$tx))
OD$tx <- factor(OD$tx, levels = c("DMSO","0.1", "0.5", "1", "2.5", "5","10","20","50","100"))

OD$Ro_conc <- as.numeric(gsub("DMSO","0", OD$tx))

return(OD)
}

Reading in data

# Read in first set of data files. OD is ELISA file. PB is presto blue file. 
OD1 <- read_csv(here("data", "ELISA", "KAB061_RoResAll.csv"))
colnames(OD1) <- c("Sample","Well","OD_450","OD_540","OD_570", "Viability_1hr")


# Read in second set of data files. OD is ELISA file. PB is presto blue file.
OD2 <- read_csv(here("data", "ELISA", "KAB064_RoResAll.csv"))
colnames(OD2) <- c("Sample","Well","OD_450","OD_540","OD_570", "Viability_1hr")

ELISA Modeling

#Use ELISAmodelfit Function to determine the amount of aldosterone produced in each experiment.
OD1 <- ELISAmodelfit(OD1)

OD1$batch <- rep("A",nrow(OD1))

OD2 <- ELISAmodelfit(OD2)

OD2$batch <- rep("B",nrow(OD2))

Dox treated, Ro Treated Cells Normalization to DMSO Control

OD <- bind_rows(OD1, OD2) #combining everything into one dataframe. 

#calculating percent aldosterone in the dox treated cells compared to DMSO control.
RoResData <- OD %>% filter(Dox=="Dox")
dmso_A_aldo <- RoResData %>% filter(batch=="A" & Ro_conc==0) %>% select(conc) %>% summarise(mean(conc)) %>% pull()
dmso_B_aldo <- RoResData %>% filter(batch=="B" & Ro_conc==0) %>% select(conc) %>% summarise(mean(conc)) %>% pull()

tmp <- mutate(RoResData, pAldo = ifelse(batch == "A", 100*conc/dmso_A_aldo, 
                                       ifelse(batch == "B", 100*conc/dmso_B_aldo, "")))
tmp$pAldo <- as.numeric(tmp$pAldo)

#calculating percent viability in the dox treated cells compared to DMSO control.
dmso_A_PB <- RoResData %>% filter(batch=="A" & Ro_conc==0) %>% select(Viability_1hr) %>% summarise(mean(Viability_1hr)) %>% pull()
dmso_B_PB <- RoResData %>% filter(batch=="B" & Ro_conc==0) %>% select(Viability_1hr) %>% summarise(mean(Viability_1hr)) %>% pull()

tmp <- mutate(tmp, pPB = ifelse(batch == "A", 100*Viability_1hr/dmso_A_PB, 
                                       ifelse(batch == "B", 100*Viability_1hr/dmso_B_PB, "")))
tmp$pPB <- as.numeric(tmp$pPB)

NoDox, Ro Treated Cells Normalization to DMSO Control

#calculating percent aldosterone in the minus dox treated cells compared to DMSO control.
NoDoxData <- OD %>% filter(Dox=="ND")
dmso_A_aldo_us <- NoDoxData %>% filter(batch=="A" & Ro_conc==0) %>% select(conc) %>% summarise(mean(conc)) %>% pull()
dmso_B_aldo_us <- NoDoxData %>% filter(batch=="B" & Ro_conc==0) %>% select(conc) %>% summarise(mean(conc)) %>% pull()

tmp_us <- mutate(NoDoxData, pAldo = ifelse(batch == "A", 100*conc/dmso_A_aldo_us, 
                                       ifelse(batch == "B", 100*conc/dmso_B_aldo_us,"")))
tmp_us$pAldo <- as.numeric(tmp_us$pAldo)

#calculating percent viability in the  minus dox treated cells compared to DMSO control.
dmso_A_PB_us <- NoDoxData %>% filter(batch=="A" & Ro_conc==0) %>% select(Viability_1hr) %>% summarise(mean(Viability_1hr)) %>% pull()
dmso_B_PB_us <- NoDoxData %>% filter(batch=="B" & Ro_conc==0) %>% select(Viability_1hr) %>% summarise(mean(Viability_1hr)) %>% pull()

tmp_us <- mutate(tmp_us, pPB = ifelse(batch == "A", 100*Viability_1hr/dmso_A_PB_us, 
                                       ifelse(batch == "B", 100*Viability_1hr/dmso_B_PB_us, "")))
tmp_us$pPB <- as.numeric(tmp_us$pPB)

Plotting Data

allData <- bind_rows(tmp, tmp_us)
p_Aldo_per <- ggline(allData, x = "Ro_conc", y = "pAldo", color = "Dox",palette = c("black","red"), ylab = "% Aldosterone", add = "mean_sd", xlab = "[Ro] uM") + rotate_x_text(60) + geom_hline(yintercept = 100, linetype = "dotted", color = "grey")
p_Aldo_per <- p_Aldo_per + ylim(-1,130)
p_Aldo_per

ggsave(plot = p_Aldo_per, filename = here("plots", "Fig2_RoRes_Aldopercent_sd.pdf"), width = 3, height = 4)

p_PB_per <- ggline(allData, x = "Ro_conc", y = "pPB", color = "Dox",palette = c("black","red"),ylab = "% Viability", add = "mean_sd", xlab = "[Ro] uM") + rotate_x_text(60) + geom_hline(yintercept = 100, linetype = "dotted", color = "grey")
p_PB_per <- p_PB_per + ylim(-1,130)
p_PB_per

ggsave(plot = p_Aldo_per, filename = "./plots/Fig2Supp_RoRes_Viabilitypercent_sd.pdf", width = 3, height = 4)
